visa_types.documents_required:
- signed visa application form;
- applicant’s valid passport/travel document;
- birth certificate + copy of all pages
- 1 applicant’s photo (35 * 45 mm);
- residence documents – valid residence permits/equivalents (in cases where applicants reside in a country that is different from the country of their nationality/citizenship);
- proof that the applicant is a holder of (or is entitled to benefit from) a valid medical/travel insurance policy to cover Ukraine and the period of stay (the policy should provide a minimum of €30 000 or equivalent coverage);
- proof of sufficient funds to cover the costs of stay (e.g. letter from the applicant’s employer confirming their coverage of applicant’s expenses in Ukraine, bank statement for 2 recent months, bank cards along with current/savings account balance statements provided the bank cards can be cashed in Ukraine, cash in Ukrainian hryvnia/other convertible currency, accommodation arrangements etc);
- a certified copy of the work permit issued by Ukraine’s State Centre for Employment (to be obtained by applicant’s employer in Ukraine in advance and sent to the applicant);
certificate of a person of Ukrainian descent* issued by Ukraine’s National Committee on Persons of Ukrainian Descent and a copy of a work/employment contract.
- Original invitation letter or letter of guarantee issued by the inviting company in Ukraine with the seal, date, signature, and name of the inviting person. Supplier, containing the complete information of the invited person's passport, travel period, frequency of travel, reason for travel, location Residency in Ukraine and... + copies (if applicable)
- Copy of the inviting person's passport (Ukrainian passport or ID card, residence card, foreign passport).... ( ) If Present
- the original work permit issued valid in Ukraine along with an equal copy of the original in Ukraine + Copycard Tax or Податків Платника Картка Documents of registration of Ukrainian company such as ВИТЯГ، виписка، свідоцтво، Статут، Опис، Договір
- Job introduction letter (containing the position, salary, date of start of work and such information (business license, advertisement) Establishment in the Official Gazette, Business Plan, etc.)If Applicable
- Proof of residence in Ukraine for at least three months, such as a hotel reservation. In the usual business invitations, the accommodation of the hotel or similar accommodations is mentioned if invited. The following documents are required for a private home or apartment:(A copy of the title deed or a document that specifies the status of its ownership, such as власності право про свідоцтво, ВИТЯГ,..... or технический паспорт
- If the owner of the property and the invitee are different: Copy of the owner's passport + manual consent from the owner with the name and information of the guest and the duration of the trip
- If the owner and the inviter do not have a relationship with each other, it is better for the property owner to send an invitation letter to the applicant. Send a separate notarization to stay at your home
- Valid lease + copy of the landlord's passport + manual consent from the landlord with the name and information of the guest and the duration of the trip
- Please note that applicants might be asked for additional documents by Ukraine’s visa officers (e.g. return flight tickets and other documents confirming applicants’ circumstances (to be defined by Ukraine’s visa officers of the relevant Embassy/Consulate General).

