visa_types.documents_required:
- original of receipt of payment for VISA FEE in USD made to bank account of embassy in Tehran + COPY.
- signed visa application form filled (http://visa.mfa.gov.ua/)
with 1 applicant’s photo (35 * 45 mm) glued to upper left of first page of application form;
- applicant’s valid passport/travel document with signature + COPY;
- residence documents – valid residence permits/equivalents (in cases where applicants reside in a country that is different from the country of their nationality/citizenship);
- a letter of the foreign Mass Media with a request to issue a visa to the foreign correspondent/Mass Media staff member who intends to travel to Ukraine in his/her professional capacity as a journalist;
- copies of the documents along with confirming the registration of the organization as a media.
- proof of medical/travel insurance to cover Ukraine and the period of stay (the policy should provide 30 000 euros or equivalent minimum coverage);+ COPY
- proof of address of accommodation of applicant. (Hotel booking, resort, etc.)
- round flight ticket (reservation will be enough).
- the original of official bank letter confirming that there is an adequate financial security, as per embassy the required amount is USD 45 per day. If the amount is specified in Rial, letter should include exchange rate to USD or EUR.
Please note that applicants might be asked for additional  documents by Ukraine’s visa officers (e.g. other documents confirming  applicants’ circumstances (to be defined by Ukraine’s visa officers of the  relevant Embassy/Consulate General).

